This might be a stupid question, but who in their right mind would assemble a
motor dry? Worse case for me is motor oil, then start up right away and
install. Second method is assembly lube if I plan on putting the short block
on the shelf for awhile. Seems like an awfully expensive way to tear up a set
of bearings. Why don't you just hit them with some 120 grit sand paper before
installing them? Hmmm

